title: $:/plugins/wikilabs/debug/jsontree-doc
caption: jsontree

! Introduction

The ''jsontree'' widget renders JSON data as an interactive collapsible tree. It can read JSON from a tiddler or directly from a widget variable.

Each object and array node is rendered as a collapsible `<details>` element. The expansion state of each node is persisted to a state tiddler so that the tree retains its shape across refreshes.

Objects that contain both `start` and `end` number properties display a link button. Clicking this button selects the corresponding character range in the nearest editor textarea. This is particularly useful for visualising parse trees alongside their source text.

! Content and Attributes

The content of the `<$jsontree>` widget is ignored.

|!Attribute |!Description |
|tiddler |Title of a tiddler containing JSON text |
|variable |Name of a variable containing JSON text |
|block-list |Space-separated list of object keys to hide from the tree |
|state |Tiddler title for storing the expansion state (defaults to `$:/temp/json-tree/state`) |

If both ''tiddler'' and ''variable'' are specified, ''variable'' takes precedence.

! Keyboard Modifiers

!! Select Range Button

Each object node with `start`/`end` properties shows a link icon button:

* ''Click'' — selects the corresponding text range in the editor and highlights the button
* ''Ctrl+Click'' (''Cmd+Click'' on Mac) — additionally folds all other paths, keeping only the ancestors of the clicked node open. Ctrl+clicking again restores the previous fold state.

The previous fold state is saved to `{state}/saved` and restored on the next Ctrl+click.

!! Fold Triangle

* ''Click'' — toggles the clicked node open or closed
* ''Ctrl+Click'' (''Cmd+Click'' on Mac) — toggles the clicked node and all of its children together

! CSS Classes

|!Class |!Description |
|`tc-jsontree` |Container element |
|`tc-jsontree-key` |Object key or array index label |
|`tc-jsontree-string` |String value |
|`tc-jsontree-number` |Number value |
|`tc-jsontree-boolean` |Boolean value |
|`tc-jsontree-null` |Null value |
|`tc-jsontree-value` |Indented content area of a collapsible node |
|`tc-jsontree-select-range` |Select range button |
|`tc-jsontree-select-range-active` |Currently active select range button |

! Examples

Display JSON from a tiddler:

```
<$jsontree tiddler="MyData"/>
```

Display a parse tree using `$wikify`:

```
<$wikify name="tree" text={{!!text}} output="parsetree">
	<$jsontree variable="tree"/>
</$wikify>
```

Hide specific keys from the output:

```
<$jsontree tiddler="MyData" block-list="rule start end"/>
```
